726970f.text:
Jamaica Avenue, east from Metropolitan Avenue, showing the elevated structure of the B.M.T. subway.
P. L. Sperr  May 7, 1934
726970f.folder: Jamaica Avenue & Metropolitan Avenue, Queens, NY

727387f-a.text:
Metropolitan Avenue, north side, at Jamaica Avenue and Kew Gardens Road, showing the "Twin Oaks," known in 1891 as the Maple Grove Hotel, owned by Jacob Pauswirth. Kew Gardens Road, the old Newtown Road, is on the extreme right; Jamaica Avenue is in the foreground, where the B. M. T. elevated throws its
shadow across the street.
P. L. Sperr  May 7, 1934
